// Morte - 754 voice lines

@986 = ~"Hey, chief. You okay? You playing corpse or you putting the blinds on the Dusties? I thought you was a deader for sure."~ [MO0986V]
@990 = ~"Me?" The skull seems indignant. "How about *you* start, scabbie? Who are you?"~ [MO0990V]
@996 = ~"Oh, so *now* you want to talk to Morte again, huh?"~ [MO0996V]
@997 = ~"You don't know who you are, huh? You *could* have just said, 'pike it, berk.' Well, that's okay... pretend you're a Clueless. See if I give a fig. I'm Morte. Hail, well met and all that wash."~ [MO0997V]
@999 = ~"You don't *remember?* Musta been some night you had. Better hope you didn't hurt anybody... the name's Morte. Hail, well met, and all that wash." He pauses for a moment. "Say, I *have* to ask: are you one of those Sensates into self-mutilation or did somebody give you those scars?"~ [MO0999V]
@1003 = ~"Yeah, 'an I asked you second. What's your name?"~ [MO1003V]
@1008 = ~"Man, you're tighter than a wet rope. All right, all right... *I'll* be the nice guy here... me, I'm Morte. Morte Rictusgrin. Now what name is unfortunate enough to have you as its owner?"~ [MO1008V]
@1012 = ~"You're in this dump called the Mortuary... it's this big black structure with all the architectural charm of a pregnant spider."~ [MO1012V]
@1014 = ~"Well, now I don't know about that... but the Mortuary's the closest thing to a morgue you're gonna find in this berg. Berks haul dead bodies here, bury 'em, burn 'em, and if you're *really* lucky, you get brought back to life as a slave. Not the best spot on the planes to be. If I was you, I'd dig up the nearest exit and give this place the laugh."~ [MO1014V]
@1021 = ~Pauses. "Yeah, I guess. Maybe some waster thought you was a deader and dropped you off. Yer corpse act sure had *me* fooled... maybe you should find the berk who dragged you here and put the questions to him, eh?" Morte nods. "Not bad thinking for a recently dead guy... good to see your brain-box is still in one piece."~ [MO1021V]
@1022 = ~"Yeah, it's a charmed life... except for the near-constant application of formaldehyde and stitching your limbs back when they fall off, it's paradise."~ [MO1022V]
@1023 = ~"Uh... like I said, the Mortuary. You okay, chief? You don't look too good."~ [MO1023V]
@1024 = ~"Chief, from where I'm sitting, you crawling off that slab was beating the odds. You look like you're about to settle your drinking tab, if you catch my meaning."~ [MO1024V]
@1025 = ~"Don't know what Sensates are? Oh, are *you* in for a treat! They're this group of bashers who're all about experiencing all the planes have to offer, right, including... well, forget it for now. What about those scars?"~ [MO1025V]
@1026 = ~"It's like some basher decided to paint you with a knife. You're scarred all over... even on your back, 'cept..." Pauses. "Say, you got a whole tattoo gallery on your back, berk. Spells out something..."~ [MO1026V]
@1031 = ~"Some people in this berg collect deaders off the street and sell 'em here for jink. Not a great way to make ends meet, but when ye're living in the chamber pot of the planes, yer options are pretty narrow."~ [MO1031V]
@1034 = ~"Eh... money. Jink is money. Didn't they have that where you came from?"~ [MO1034V]
@1037 = ~He pauses. "Don't know. You're *talking* to me... the walking dead around here don't usually do that. As I see it, the Dusties made a mistake and you weren't dead. Did you sign some sort of contract that you remember? I mean, they usually gotta fill out all sorts of legal paperwork before they can pull someone outta the dead-book."~ [MO1037V]
@1042 = ~"Yeah, the 'dead-book.' You know? Uh, maybe you don't. Look, forget the 'dead-book.' You're alive, so you ain't in it."~ [MO1042V]
@1043 = ~"Yeah, don't it make you want to split bricks? Law makes Sigil spin, and you can't even empty your bladder without filling out one contract or another."~ [MO1043V]
@1044 = ~"By every god and his mother, are *you* out of it. Do you have any idea where you came from? Somewhere, a nation of Clueless is missing their king. Did you bite your thumb at a god or were you always this ignorant?"~ [MO1044V]
@1045 = ~"Chief, I have no sodding idea. You sure got the knack for playing dead, though. While you was lying there, I never saw your chest move, your eyes blink... nothing. Were you drinking? Is that what happened?"~ [MO1045V]
@1046 = ~"Well, now that *is* a good question. Sand's running through the glass for you, chief. The Dustmen find you, they'll attempt to correct your resurrection 'problem' by tossing you in the crematorium. If you keep playing dead, you'll go to the crematorium anyway. A modron's choice, eh? What to do?"~ [MO1046V]
@1052 = ~"Oh, *good* idea, chief! Why didn't *I* think of that? How you gonna escape, huh? I'll give you a clue: It involves a little cooperation."~ [MO1052V]
@1055 = ~"From where I'm sitting, it's obvious you need to get out of here. Me, I can afford to wait. The only danger *I'm* in is dying of boredom. We could lend each other a hand."~ [MO1055V]
@1061 = ~"It may not look it, but I could help you outta here, and you could help me outta here. I haven't got hands, so I'm in a bit of a quandary. You're missing what's in your cranium, while I got plenty of experience and know-how to get you out of this dive. We cooperate, and we both come out a *head.* Deal, berk?"~ [MO1061V]
@1064 = ~"Oh, *good* idea, chief! Why didn't *I* think of that?" His tone becomes mocking. "By the way, Sir Dustman, I died and woke up on a slab in your little Mortuary. Can you please help me?" "They'll 'help' you all right. They'll look at you for a few seconds, call the guards and pop you in your own private kiln."~ [MO1064V]
@1068 = ~"Just trust me... it doesn't matter how tough you think you are or what you say to them, they'll get you. You ain't strong enough to break out of a walled-in tomb or survive the heat of the Elemental Plane of Fire. Waking up from the dead is bad enough as far as the caretakers around here are concerned. Don't be an idiot."~ [MO1068V]
@1071 = ~"Fate can go squat on a halberd for all I care. Listen, chief. Pay attention to how often 'bad' and 'fate' show up in the same sentence, and you'll catch on to one of life's little mysteries. Best thing to do is to tell fate to wrap itself in razorvine; there's *always* another option that fate never lets on."~ [MO1071V]
@1072 = ~"Awright then... now, c'mon, let's give this place the laugh. The doors outta here are locked, so we'll need the key. Chances are, one of the walking corpses in this room has it."~ [MO1072V]
@1082 = ~"The Dusties? They watch the place here. You can't miss them... they have an obsession with black and rigor mortis of the face. They call themselves 'the Dustmen' and pretend they're a faction, but they're just an addled bunch of ghoulish death-worshippers. Steer clear of them."~ [MO1082V]
@1091 = ~"Yeah? Like *what* questions?"~ [MO1091V]
@1100 = ~"You don't remember *anything?* C'mon, that's a load of tanar'ri dung. You serious?"~ [MO1100V]
@1104 = ~"By every god and his mother... well, chief, more than likely your memories just took a dive into your brain-box. With any luck, they'll come up for air soon, trust me. Musta been some night you had. Better hope you didn't hurt anybody or mix it up with the law... say, speaking of which, are you one of those Sensates into self-mutilation or did somebody give you those scars?"~ [MO1104V]
@1117 = ~"Looks like directions..." Morte clears his throat. "Let's see. It starts with..."  NOTE: "I know you feel like you've been drinking a few kegs of Styx wash, but you need to center yourself. Among your possessions should be a JOURNAL that'll shed some light on the dark of the matter. PHAROD should be able to fill you in on the rest of the chant, if he's not in the dead-book already.   Don't lose this scrap of flesh OR the journal or we'll be up the Styx again, right? And trust me, whatever you do, DO NOT tell anyone WHO you are, WHAT happens to you, or WHERE you came from or you'll find yourself on a short trip to the crematorium."~ [MO1117V]
@1123 = ~"No... you were stripped to the skins when you arrived here. 'Sides, looks like you got enough of a journal written on your body."~ [MO1123V]
@1128 = ~"Nobody I know. Then again, I don't know many people. Still, some berk's got to know where to find this guy... once we get out of here, that is."~ [MO1128V]
@1818 = ~"What good fortune! We probably lost what we're looking for back at your kip, miss."~ [MO1818V]
@1844 = ~"Chief, can you sport me some jink... it's... eh... been a long time, it has."~ [MO1844V]
@2000 = ~"She means money."~ [MO2000V]
@2048 = ~"It's just as well neither you nor your tail are for sale. You couldn't squeak out a living with 'em, anyway."~ [MO2048V]
@2067 = ~"She's a tiefling, chief. They got some demon's blood in 'em, and that makes 'em paranoid and defensive... nice tail, though. Shame it's plastered on such an ugly body."~ [MO2067V]
@2074 = ~"Why don't you *try* and split my jaw, chit?! All I'm hearing is a lotta chatter from some Hive trash! Throw a punch! I dare you! I'll bite your legs off!"~ [MO2074V]
@2079 = ~"Mimir's a talking encyclopedia. That's me, chief."~ [MO2079V]
@2348 = ~"Give it up, chief. Talking to a gith is like trying to make good with razorvine. Let's go."~ [MO2348V]
@2349 = ~"Yeah, a 'gith'..." Morte glances at the gith, who is still staring at you. "We'll talk about it some other time."~ [MO2349V]
@2354 = ~"I wouldn't bother trying to talk square to ol' Ignorance-is-Bliss here. Let's get outta here, chief."~ [MO2354V]
@2601 = ~"Psssst. You see the way she was looking at me? Huh? You see that? The way she was following the curve of my occipital bone?"~ [MO2601V]
@2604 = ~"Wha- are you BLIND?! She was scouting me out! It was shameless the way she WANTED me."~ [MO2604V]
@2609 = ~"Yeah, yeah, whatever. When you've been dead as long as I have, you know the signals. They may be too SUBTLE for you to pick up on, but that's why I'll be spending MY nights with some luscious recently-dead chit while you're standing around goin' 'huh?' 'Whatzz goin' on?' 'Where's my muh-muh-memories?'"~ [MO2609V]
@2611 = ~"You? Yeah, right! Trust me, chits beyond the grave don't care about all that 'physicality' and 'I've got a body' and 'I'm all scarred and tough-looking.' They want guys with SPIRIT. That's me, chief. You? Corpses like YOU are as common as copper."~ [MO2611V]
@2709 = ~"What? What is it? Is this chit bothering you?"~ [MO2709V]
@2711 = ~"I believe it. Maybe he'd better return to your main menu and leave me out of it."~ [MO2711V]
@2782 = ~"Oh, for the powers' sake! Piking dabus."~ [MO2782V]
@2788 = ~"He's a dabus. They 'speak' in rebuses, these annoying word puzzles. If *you* don't know what he's saying, then we better find a native or some other way to communicate with him... if we want to. An annoying bunch. My bet? They *can* speak, they just would rather piss everyone else off by trying to puzzle out what they're saying."~ [MO2788V]
@2789 = ~"Chant is they're janitors for the Lady of Pain. They float around breaking, fixing and patching up Sigil according to her whims. They're worse than corpse flies." Morte sighs. "You can't swat 'em though, or the Lady'll get... upset."~ [MO2789V]
@3473 = ~"I think the Dustie chit might be a bit short of hearing, chief. Let's lay off, shall we?"~ [MO3473V]
@3477 = ~"Eh... she's a *tiefling,* chief. They got fiend blood in their veins, usually 'cause some ancestor of theirs shared knickers with one demon or another. Makes some of 'em addled in the head... and addled-looking, too."~ [MO3477V]
@3480 = ~"I think the Dustie chit might be a bit short of hearing, chief. Let's lay off, shall we?"~ [MO3480V]
@3481 = ~"Eh... she's a *tiefling,* chief. They got a dash of fiend blood running in their veins, usually 'cause some ancestor of theirs shared knickers with some demon or another. Makes some of 'em addled in the head... and usually addled-looking, too."~ [MO3481V]
@3487 = ~"Looks like you have a new friend, chief. You two need some time together, or...?"~ [MO3487V]
@3492 = ~"This may be the second time in my life I'm thankful I don't have a nose."~ [MO3492V]
@3870 = ~"Hey! Hey! What are you doing?"~ [MO3870V]
@3873 = ~"If you're going to rattle your bone-box with Dusties, leave me outta it. Me and them aren't gonna be best bloods... and you shouldn't try and be family with them either. They'd sooner torch or bury you than bend an ear. Don't be barmy; let's just get out of here."~ [MO3873V]
@3876 = ~"Hey! Are you deaf? What are you doing?"~ [MO3876V]
@3879 = ~"*Don't* listen to me then - it's your funeral."~ [MO3879V]
@3964 = ~"Whoa, chief. That's vandalism. Those bolts are probably the only thing holding that bag of bones together. Necromancy only goes so far with these old fellas, y'know?"~ [MO3964V]
@3968 = ~"Oh, it's not a problem." Morte does a strange bobbing motion that you think might be a shrug. "Just wasn't sure if you knew that or not. By all means, go ahead."~ [MO3968V]
@3974 = ~"Hmmmm. Wonder if this graybeard would mind if *I* borrowed his body..."~ [MO3974V]
@3978 = ~"Graybeard... you know, geezer, old feller, yellow dog... old."~ [MO3978V]
@3981 = ~Morte studies the skeleton for a moment, then shakes his head. "Nah... I'd need a fresher one than this. And something with a little more dignity... this one's all creaky and fractured."~ [MO3981V]
@3984 = ~"Oh, you're a sackfull of laughs." Morte glares at you. "Besides, YOU'RE one to talk, berk. Mirrors beg for mercy when you're around."~ [MO3984V]
@3987 = ~Morte snorts. You're not quite sure how he managed it without lungs.~ [MO3987V]
@3990 = ~"Helping you escape the preparation room has now been added to my growing list of regrets." Morte snorts again. "I should have let you rot... more, that is."~ [MO3990V]
@4018 = ~Morte grins.~ [MO4018V]
@4020 = ~"Oh... sorry." Morte floats up to the head of the skeleton, stares at it, then floats back down, studying the armor and the blade as he descends. "Oh, yes. Yes, yes, I think this'll do."~ [MO4020V]
@4021 = ~"Then what in Baator did you ASK me if I wanted it for, then? Practicing your cruelty skills?" Morte bobs indignantly. "And after all I've done for you..."~ [MO4021V]
@4022 = ~Morte stares at you for a moment. "What, did we get MARRIED at some point? What's all this 'I don't want you to get hurt' wash?" Morte glares at you. "If you REALLY cared, you'd find a way to get my head on that giant skeleton's body."~ [MO4022V]
@4134 = ~"Hey! Hey! What are you doing?"~ [MO4134V]
@4135 = ~"If you're going to rattle your bone-box with Dusties, leave me outta it. Me and them aren't gonna be best bloods... and you shouldn't try and be family with them either. They'd sooner torch or bury you than bend an ear. Don't be barmy; let's just get out of here."~ [MO4135V]
@4136 = ~"Hey! Are you deaf? What are you doing?"~ [MO4136V]
@4137 = ~"*Don't* listen to me then - it's your funeral."~ [MO4137V]
@4338 = ~"Hey! Hey! What are you doing?"~ [MO4338V]
@4341 = ~"If you're going to rattle your bone-box with Dusties, leave me outta it. Me and them aren't gonna be best bloods... and you shouldn't try and be family with them either. They'd sooner torch or bury you than bend an ear. Don't be barmy; let's just get out of here."~ [MO4341V]
@4344 = ~"Hey! Are you deaf? What are you doing?"~ [MO4344V]
@4347 = ~"*Don't* listen to me then - it's your funeral."~ [MO4347V]
@4675 = ~Morte breaks in, whispering. "By the powers... this berk's an *Anarchist.* Posing as a zombie's got to be a first for those addled sods."~ [MO4675V]
@4677 = ~"Anarchists... they're a faction..." Morte looks like he's about to let loose a torrent of insults, then notices the zombie staring at you both, listening intently. "...they, uh, want to *liberate* everyone from the chains of government. Tear down the old, establish a new order with no order at all."~ [MO4677V]
@4683 = ~Whispers: "He's wondering if you're crazy, loco, a cackle, addled... and so am I. Now stow the 'I woke up from the dead' talk, willya?! Ye're embarrassing me."~ [MO4683V]
@4688 = ~Morte sighs. "Look, chief... you gotta get your wits about you. You can't go around telling everybody the TRUTH all the time. We can't have every cony-catcher we meet taking us for marks, right?"~ [MO4688V]
@4692 = ~"Hold on..." Morte sounds surprised. "This berk must be an *Anarchist.* Heh. Posing as a zombie's got to be a first for those addled sods."~ [MO4692V]
@4694 = ~"Anarchists... they're a faction that wastes their time peeping on authority figures and looking for ways to tear down anything that stinks of order or control." Morte snorts. "The Anarchists think every berk across the planes'll be free and happy to seek out their own 'truth' once the establishment is burned to the ground. They want to establish a new order - no order at all."~ [MO4694V]
@4700 = ~"He's saying this Pharod berk has been selling a lot of deaders... corpses... to the Dustmen. That's what Collectors do: they gather dead bodies and sell them to the Dustmen. Sounds like this Pharod's been selling so many deaders that the Dusties think he's been putting Hivers in the dead-book before their hour's up... y'know, killing people."~ [MO4700V]
@4703 = ~"He wants to know if somebody robbed you. Probably what happened."~ [MO4703V]
@4706 = ~"Yeah, *they're* the stupid ones all right."~ [MO4706V]
@4708 = ~"I can't believe you're going through with this. How barmy ARE you?"~ [MO4708V]
@4710 = ~"Can't you make the stitches on his lips any tighter?"~ [MO4710V]
@5029 = ~"Hey! Hey! What are you doing?"~ [MO5029V]
@5032 = ~"If you're going to rattle your bone-box with Dusties, leave me outta it. Me and them aren't gonna be best bloods... and you shouldn't try and be family with them either. They'd sooner torch or bury you than bend an ear. Don't be barmy; let's just get out of here."~ [MO5032V]
@5035 = ~"Hey! Are you deaf? What are you doing?"~ [MO5035V]
@5038 = ~"*Don't* listen to me then - it's your funeral."~ [MO5038V]
@5041 = ~"What are you *doing?!* If you're gonna kill him, do it!"~ [MO5041V]
@5043 = ~"At least he *can* walk." Morte snorts. "Floating around loses its thrill as soon as you want to kick somebody."~ [MO5043V]
@5049 = ~"Whoa, chief! What are you doing?!"~ [MO5049V]
@5052 = ~"Look, rattling your bone-box with Dusties should be the LAST thing-"~ [MO5052V]
@5053 = ~"And we *especially* shouldn't be swapping the chant with sick Dusties. C'mon, let's leave. The quicker we give this place the laugh, the bet-"~ [MO5053V]
@6071 = ~"You back with me, chief? You kind of drifted out on me there."~ [MO6071V]
@6072 = ~"Eh? Spirit?"~ [MO6072V]
@6073 = ~"You were rattling your bone-box with some woman? Where?" Morte looks around, excited. "What did she look like?"~ [MO6073V]
@6074 = ~"Eh... no, you just kind of drifted out for a bit there, just stood there, statue-like. I was a little worried you'd gone addled on me again."~ [MO6074V]
@6324 = ~"Reminds me of a job I once had." He seems embarrassed. "Well, I mean... without the arms."~ [MO6324V]
@6609 = ~"Whoa, chief. That's vandalism. Those bolts are probably the only thing holding that bag of bones together. Necromancy only goes so far with these old fellas, y'know?"~ [MO6609V]
@6610 = ~"Hmmmm. Wonder if this graybeard would mind if *I* borrowed his body..."~ [MO6610V]
@6611 = ~"Would you cut that out? His arms are gonna snap off."~ [MO6611V]
@6771 = ~"She runs this city. You'll know if you see her: She's got these blades around her face, she's about the size of a giant, and she floats off the ground, just like these guys." Morte nods at the dabus, who is looking at you both. "Nobody knows much about her... she doesn't speak much. All you need to know is that you don't want to make her angry. If you see her, my advice: run."~ [MO6771V]
@6784 = ~Morte scoffs. "I'd sooner be strained through a tanar'ri's bowels than unravel what these floating goat-heads are trying to say. You want a translator? Find a Sigil native."~ [MO6784V]
@6786 = ~"Oh, they *have* names. I'm sure of it."~ [MO6786V]
@6790 = ~"So *you* say, fiendling."~ [MO6790V]
@6794 = ~Morte scoffs. "I'd sooner be strained through a tanar'ri's bowels than unravel what these floating goat-heads are trying to say. You want a translator? Get the fiendling chit here to do it." He nods at Annah. "She's a Hive native."~ [MO6794V]
@6797 = ~Morte scoffs. "I'd sooner be strained through a tanar'ri's bowels than unravel what these floating goat-heads are trying to say. You want a translator?" He nods at Dak'kon. "Get holier-than-thou-and-twice-as-silent here to translate."~ [MO6797V]
@6800 = ~Morte scoffs. "I'd sooner be strained through a tanar'ri's bowels than unravel what these floating goat-heads are trying to say. You want a translator? Get the tanar'ri to do it." He nods at Fall-from-Grace. "She's probably had to trade the chant with these guys all the time."~ [MO6800V]
@7040 = ~As you turn away, you notice Morte staring at you. "Eh? Eh?"~ [MO7040V]
@7041 = ~"Did you *see* the way that cadaverous beauty was staring at me?" Morte's teeth chatter, as if in anticipation. "She was looking for some lucky cutter to thaw her coffin."~ [MO7041V]
@7042 = ~Morte ignores you and becomes thoughtful. "I don't really mind the attention, actually... it's just that I like to be seen as something more than just a skull, y'know? I have feelings that go beyond my base animal instincts. I want courtship, not some fortnight fling around the mausoleum."~ [MO7042V]
@7043 = ~"Whoa, chief..." Morte backs slightly out of arm's reach. "Women, they appreciate lovers, not fighters."~ [MO7043V]
@7044 = ~"Yeah, well, I may be just a skull, but I've got a big heart."~ [MO7044V]
@7045 = ~"What, were you dumped into my life to spit on my dreams and aspirations?! Fine, be that way, then. I don't have a heart, but I *do* have a soul."~ [MO7045V]
@7046 = ~"If you had half the sense you died with, you'd know better." Morte's voice rises to new heights of smugness. "When it comes to the annals of love, I wrote 'em all."~ [MO7046V]
@7071 = ~Morte studies the skeleton for a moment, then shakes his head. "Nah... this one's too clean... there's barely any meat left on him at all. Plus, I'd never be able to get all that whitewash off the bones."~ [MO7071V]
@7130 = ~"Yeah!"~ [MO7130V]
@7187 = ~"Mimir's a talking encyclopedia. That's me, chief."~ [MO7187V]
@7775 = ~"Whoa, chief." Morte cuts in before you can speak to the creature. "Bar that. You don't want to be rattling your bone-box with any fiend on the street. Leave be."~ [MO7775V]
@7778 = ~"No you don't." Morte glances at the creature, then turns back to you and lowers his voice to a whisper. "They're touchy. Let's just go."~ [MO7778V]
@7805 = ~Morte sighs as you are about to speak to the creature.~ [MO7805V]
@7807 = ~"Oh, nothing... life is the best teacher, you know." He nods at the creature. "Go ahead."~ [MO7807V]
@9860 = ~"C'mon, chief... you'll kill the sod before you manage to wake him!"~ [MO9860V]
@11946 = ~Morte floats over. "What's the chant, chief?"~ [MO11946V]
@11947 = ~Morte glances at your palm. "Yechhhh." He seems morbidly fascinated. "Ugly little berks, aren't they?"~ [MO11947V]
@11948 = ~"Bar that." Morte shudders. "Would you want those things in *you?*"~ [MO11948V]
@11949 = ~"Those little pikers better not come anywhere near me, or I'll..." Morte pauses. "You know, I have no idea how to threaten teeth."~ [MO11949V]
@11950 = ~The struggle is brief. You catch Morte in a headlock - the only move you can really do - and as he attempts to bite his way free, the teeth hop out of your hand and swarm onto his jaw. Morte howls as Ingress' teeth promptly rip out his old teeth and then jump into the exposed cavities.~ [MO11950V]
@11951 = ~Morte continues howling. The teeth settle in, adjusting themselves and planting their roots with a horrid drilling noise.~ [MO11951V]
@11952 = ~Morte doesn't seem to hear you... he keeps howling and howling, then suddenly starts smashing his teeth together. He gets in three powerful bites before the upper and lower teeth lock together and prevent him from opening his mouth.~ [MO11952V]
@11953 = ~Morte mumbles something at you, his eyes wide.~ [MO11953V]
@11954 = ~The teeth suddenly unlock, and Morte takes a deep breath. "I will *kill* you for this," he says. "That was a dirty thing to do."~ [MO11954V]
@11955 = ~Morte moves his jaw around experimentally. "Odd. But not bad." Suddenly, the teeth extend into fangs. "Ooooooh! They change!" They shrink down to normal, then fangs again, then normal... "I think I'm going to like these."~ [MO11955V]
@11956 = ~"Oh, I'll still get you for this," Morte replies. He grins, his teeth turning into fangs again. "Just you wait."~ [MO11956V]
@11957 = ~"What's wrong?" Morte floats in closer and glances at your palm. "Hey... they look like they're planning something, don't they?"~ [MO11957V]
@11958 = ~What happens next is difficult to describe... and painful to watch. Faster than you can close your palm, the teeth hop out of your hand and swarm onto Morte's jaw. Morte howls as Ingress' teeth promptly rip out his old teeth and then jump into the exposed cavities.~ [MO11958V]
@11959 = ~The teeth suddenly unlock, and Morte takes a deep breath. "I will *kill* you for this! You planned that! I know it!"~ [MO11959V]
@12389 = ~Morte whispers to you: "Boss, I don't like this. They're not supposed to be here. The Blood War hasn't kicked the celestials' asses bad enough that any fiend can go on furlough. They *want* something. Tread carefully." In the meantime, Tegar'in continues to respond to its companion...~ [MO12389V]
@12449 = ~"Boss, I'm more sure than ever that these berks ain't on the up and up. Sounds to me like they deserted, like they're looking for some angle that'll elevate their status in Baator. You don't want to be talking to 'em, boss... you don't know what game they're playing, and you could get burned... literally."~ [MO12449V]
@12466 = ~Morte floats close to whisper in your ear: "He *is* right, chief... I don't know what's got you all riled up."~ [MO12466V]
@12467 = ~"Yeah, yeah! The good stuff!"~ [MO12467V]
@12621 = ~Morte seems taken aback as all eyes fall on him. "What? What?" You get the impression that, had he lips, he'd be whistling innocently.~ [MO12621V]
@12622 = ~"Well, I say we hear this man out. Yeah?" Morte turns and stares hard at the rat-catcher.~ [MO12622V]
@12623 = ~Morte rolls his eyes, as if embarrassed. "It's a... talking encyclopedia. Not something I'm proud of. Now, let's hear this fellow out, all right?"~ [MO12623V]
@12624 = ~"Oh c'mon, chief... why would I hold out on you? I've told you everything useful *I* know. Let's just get this berk's take on the whole thing."~ [MO12624V]
@12625 = ~"Yeah, chief! That's the spirit!"~ [MO12625V]
@12626 = ~"Dead, chief... dead."~ [MO12626V]
@12627 = ~"Dead, chief... dead."~ [MO12627V]
@13748 = ~"Well, that's a tree with one snapped branch too many." Morte rolls his eyes. "No sense in chatting with Xaositects, chief. They're a barmy bunch."~ [MO13748V]
@13749 = ~"They're a 'faction' who don't have any rules... except don't keep one thought in their head for too long. They're sometimes called 'Chaosmen.' No need to explain why."~ [MO13749V]
@13750 = ~"They just seem to attract members like flies... well, members that are crazy or chaotic enough, I suppose. I don't think they have any recruiters... though you really can't say anything about them for sure."~ [MO13750V]
@13828 = ~"Well, that's a tree with one snapped branch too many." Morte rolls his eyes. "No sense in chatting with Xaositects, chief. They're a barmy bunch."~ [MO13828V]
@13829 = ~"They're a 'faction' who don't have any rules... except don't keep one thought in their head for too long. They're sometimes called 'Chaosmen.' No need to explain why."~ [MO13829V]
@13830 = ~"They just seem to attract members like flies... well, members that are crazy or chaotic enough, I suppose. I don't think they have any recruiters... though you really can't say anything about them for sure."~ [MO13830V]
@14075 = ~"All rightie then..." Morte hisses at you. "Let's go, chief. This Dustie might as well be fertilizer."~ [MO14075V]
@15339 = ~"Tear that candied fop in two, boss! Show him how it's done!"~ [MO15339V]
@15340 = ~"Yeah, answer the questions!"~ [MO15340V]
@15341 = ~"I'll put ten copper on the big, scarred guy!" Morte floats close and whispers: "Eh, that's you, chief. Don't let us down, here."~ [MO15341V]
@15342 = ~"All right, chief: you've got him this time! Fight dirty!"~ [MO15342V]
@15343 = ~"That's right, you pompous, perfumed, candied-arse elitist... you heard him!"~ [MO15343V]
@15344 = ~"Who am *I?* Hah! I could've been your father but that monkey beat me up the stairs!"~ [MO15344V]
@15345 = ~"What's wrong, princess? At a loss for words? You'd best lift that dropped jaw before something flies down your throat! That's right, you heard me! Pack up your frilly brassiere and go hide beneath your mother's filthy skirt, where you belong! And tell her I said hello while you're at it!"~ [MO15345V]
@15346 = ~"Huh? Oh... sorry, chief. This kind of guy just gets to me..."~ [MO15346V]
@15347 = ~"Why, if I didn't know any better, I'd say-"~ [MO15347V]
@15348 = ~"What? I'm just a mimir, chief! I can't 'duel!'"~ [MO15348V]
@15349 = ~"It's, uh... sort of a talking encyclopedia. I don't like to talk about it; sort of embarrassing, really."~ [MO15349V]
@15350 = ~"Come on, chief... you going to let him get away with that? Let's go trounce that prissy rake! I'll go for his eyes while you lay into him!"~ [MO15350V]
@16613 = ~"Huh? Oh, yeah, chief, sure - whatever you say."~ [MO16613V]
@16614 = ~Morte looks at you for a while, silently, then nods. "Yeah, I can. If it's that important to you, I'll do it."~ [MO16614V]
@16615 = ~"You know, I *really* can't see this going anywhere. It's the old blood from a stone thing, chief - these little guys just don't work that way."~ [MO16615V]
@16616 = ~"Oh, boy; here we go. I can't *believe* you're wasting your time like this, boss!"~ [MO16616V]
@16617 = ~"You know, chief, I've seen some weird stuff... but it boggles my mind that that was even *possible.*"~ [MO16617V]
@16618 = ~"Oh! I can't watch!"~ [MO16618V]
@17533 = ~"Why not, boss? It'll be fun to kick around when we're down, right? Hmm... Well, I can kick it vicariously through you, at least. I wanna see that fifteen-foot hot coal jump, too!"~ [MO17533V]
@18801 = ~Morte turns to the Hiver. "Pike off."~ [MO18801V]
@18809 = ~Morte is holding one of the man's fingers between his teeth like some macabre cigar. He speaks around the finger: "Touch me again, and yer hand's gonna join yer finger, berk."~ [MO18809V]
@18813 = ~Morte spits the finger at the man. It bounces off the man's chest and falls to the ground.~ [MO18813V]
@18816 = ~Morte spins to face you: "Chief, don't give this trash anything."~ [MO18816V]
@18818 = ~Morte turns on the man. "I *wasn't* talking to you, arse-for-brains. When I talk to you, you'll know, 'cause I'll be grunting and snorting so you can understand what I'm saying."~ [MO18818V]
@18819 = ~"Chief, *don't.*"~ [MO18819V]
@18826 = ~"I'm floating with the biggest idiot in the multiverse."~ [MO18826V]
@18831 = ~"Chief! C'mon!"~ [MO18831V]
@18832 = ~"None too pretty from where I'm floating, either."~ [MO18832V]
@19031 = ~"Hey there, big hitter! How's your friend in the wall?"~ [MO19031V]
@19032 = ~Morte ducks his head. "Whatever you say, boss."~ [MO19032V]
@19551 = ~"Wow, chief... what a beauty, eh? Not everywhere you can meet a sweet little chit like that, ya know."~ [MO19551V]
@19552 = ~Morte's eyes roll in his skull. "Huh! One day, you'll see what I mean."~ [MO19552V]
@19553 = ~"Yeah, see, that's what I'm... hey!" Morte spins to face you. "Are you getting sarcastic on me?"~ [MO19553V]
@19681 = ~"Eh... don't know if you want to be talking to that... thing."~ [MO19681V]
@19682 = ~"They were once humans... they, or their ancestors, feasted on corpses, and this is what they've become. Pretty nasty stuff, chief... they're little more than animals, really. *Dangerous* animals."~ [MO19682V]
@19702 = ~"Eh... don't know if you want to be talking to that... thing."~ [MO19702V]
@19703 = ~"They were once humans... they, or their ancestors, feasted on corpses, and this is what they've become. Pretty nasty stuff, chief... they're little more than animals, really. *Dangerous* animals."~ [MO19703V]
@19704 = ~"It's not quite the same thing, chief..."~ [MO19704V]
@20469 = ~"This gravebait's blind and near-deaf."~ [MO20469V]
@20470 = ~"I think she means organs. I hope she means organs."~ [MO20470V]
@20471 = ~Morte turns to Marta. "Yes, 'thingies.'" He then turns to you. "It's all semantics."~ [MO20471V]
@20472 = ~"I am *not* going to watch this."~ [MO20472V]
@21602 = ~"Oh, for the powers' sake...! Piking dabus."~ [MO21602V]
@21603 = ~"He's a dabus. They 'speak' in rebuses, these annoying word puzzles. If *you* don't know what he's saying, then we better find a native or some other way to communicate with him... if we want to. An annoying bunch. My bet? They *can* speak, they just would rather piss everyone else off by trying to puzzle out what they're saying."~ [MO21603V]
@21604 = ~"Chant is they're janitors for the Lady of Pain. They float around breaking, fixing and patching up Sigil according to her whims. They're worse than corpse flies." Morte sighs. "You can't swat 'em though, or the Lady'll get... upset."~ [MO21604V]
@21605 = ~"She runs this city. You'll know if you see her: She's got these blades around her face, she's about the size of a giant, and she floats off the ground, just like these guys." Morte nods at the dabus, who is looking at you both. "Nobody knows much about her... she doesn't speak much. All you need to know is that you don't want to make her angry. If you see her, my advice: run."~ [MO21605V]
@21606 = ~Morte glances at the dabus, and his eyes widen. "Ah-ha! I knew you goat-heads could walk! I knew it!" Morte turns gleefully back to you. "Ha! This one must not be aloof enough to get off the ground."~ [MO21606V]
@21607 = ~Morte scoffs. "I'd sooner be strained through a tanar'ri's bowels than unravel what this goat-head's trying to say. You want a translator? Find a Sigil native."~ [MO21607V]
@21608 = ~Morte scoffs. "I'd sooner be strained through a tanar'ri's bowels than unravel what these floating goat-heads are trying to say. You want a translator? Get the fiendling chit to do it." He nods at Annah. "She's a Hive native."~ [MO21608V]
@21609 = ~Morte scoffs. "I'd sooner be strained through a tanar'ri's bowels than unravel what these floating goat-heads are trying to say. You want a translator?" He nods at Dak'kon. "Get holier-than-thou-and-twice-as-silent to translate."~ [MO21609V]
@21610 = ~Morte scoffs. "I'd sooner be strained through a tanar'ri's bowels than unravel what these floating goat-heads are trying to say. You want a translator? Get the tanar'ri to do it." He nods at Fall-from-Grace. "She's probably had to trade the chant with these guys all the time."~ [MO21610V]
@22061 = ~"You just want to kill them. Sentience threatens the Dustmen."~ [MO22061V]
@22849 = ~Morte stares at you and shakes his head.~ [MO22849V]
@22852 = ~"Hey! It didn't say that!"~ [MO22852V]
@22855 = ~"Wh-?! Gimme that thing!"~ [MO22855V]
@22858 = ~"I. Just. Want. To. Hold. It. For. A. Second."~ [MO22858V]
@22861 = ~"I'll hold it in my TEETH."~ [MO22861V]
@24174 = ~"You know, boss, I was getting really sick of his... constant... pauses... anyway... it's a ... good thing... he's shut up... now."~ [MO24174V]
@24176 = ~"Boss, what do we need with an endless supply of water? Where's the fire, huh?"~ [MO24176V]
@24179 = ~"The right thing to do? In case you've forgotten, boss, you've got a quest of your own to take care of! But hey, whatever you want to do, you're in charge here. Sheesh..."~ [MO24179V]
@24903 = ~"Hey... are you all right? I thought you were a deader for sure."~ [MO24903V]
@24906 = ~"Uh... who am I? How about *you* start? Who're you?"~ [MO24906V]
@24909 = ~"You can't remember your *name?* Heh. Well, next time you spend a night on the town, go easy on the bub. Name's Morte. I'm trapped in here, too."~ [MO24909V]
@24911 = ~"Yeah, 'an I asked you *second.* What's your name?"~ [MO24911V]
@24914 = ~"Tchhhh... you're tighter than a wet rope. All right, *I'll* be the nice guy here. Name's Morte. Who're you?"~ [MO24914V]
@24916 = ~"Yeah, since you haven't had time to get your legs yet, here's the chant: I've tried all the doors, and this room is locked tighter than a chastity belt."~ [MO24916V]
@24918 = ~"It's called the 'Mortuary'... it's a big black structure with all the architectural charm of a pregnant spider."~ [MO24918V]
@24920 = ~"Not from where I'm standing. You got scars a-plenty, though... looks like some berk painted you with a knife. All the more reason to give this place the laugh before whoever carved you up comes back to finish the job."~ [MO24920V]
@24922 = ~"Well, all the doors are locked, so we'll need the key. Chances are, one of the walking corpses in this room have it."~ [MO24922V]
@24924 = ~"Yeah, the Mortuary keepers use dead bodies as cheap labor. The corpses are dumb as stones, but they're harmless, and won't attack you unless you attack first."~ [MO24924V]
@24927 = ~"What, you think it's going to hurt their feelings? They're DEAD. But if you want a bright side to this: if you kill them, at least they'll have a rest before their keepers raise them up to work again."~ [MO24927V]
@24929 = ~"Well, before you do that, arm yourself first. I think there's a scalpel on one of the shelves around here."  ^NNOTE: Search the shelves in this room for a weapon to attack the zombies with.^-~ [MO24929V]
@24931 = ~"One last thing: Those corpses are as slow as molasses, but getting punched by one of them is like being kissed by a battering ram. If they start getting an edge on you, remember you can RUN, and they can't. Use it to keep some distance if you need to recover."  ^NNOTE: <RUNAWAY> If you are in danger of dying, use running to keep your distance from the zombies while you recover.^-~ [MO24931V]
@25962 = ~"Sort of a talking encyclopedia, chief. I don't like to talk about it, really."~ [MO25962V]
@25964 = ~Morte waggles his eyebrows and begins to float towards the woman. "That's not all I-"~ [MO25964V]
@25966 = ~"Yeah, yeah. Fine." Morte rolls his eyes and starts to mumble. "Sheesh, I might as well be *dead*..."~ [MO25966V]
@25970 = ~Morte interrupts her: "Well, you see, chief, it's all about differences in the *quality* of your mimir. Some - like me - are more enchanted than others, that's all. More... uh... 'self-aware,' is the term."~ [MO25970V]
@25973 = ~"Hey! I'm just trying to have some fun here, chief!"~ [MO25973V]
@27285 = ~"Some advice, chief: I'd keep it quiet from here on - no need to put any more corpses in the dead-book than necessary... especially the femmes. Plus, killing them might draw the caretakers here."~ [MO27285V]
@27286 = ~"They call themselves the 'Dustmen.' You can't miss 'em: They have an obsession with black and rigor mortis of the face. They're an addled bunch of ghoulish death-worshippers; they believe everybody should die... sooner better than later."~ [MO27286V]
@27287 = ~"Weren't you listening?! I said the Dusties believe EVERYBODY'S got to die, sooner better than later. You think the corpses you've seen are happier in the dead-book than out of it?"~ [MO27287V]
@27288 = ~"Death visits the planes every day, chief. These lummoxes are all that's left of the poor sods who sold their bodies to the caretakers after death."~ [MO27288V]
@27289 = ~"Wh- are you *serious?* Look, chief, these dead chits are the last chance for a couple of hardy bashers like us. We need to be *chivalrous*... no hacking them up for keys, no lopping their limbs off, things like that."~ [MO27289V]
@27290 = ~"Chief, THEY'RE dead, WE'RE dead... see where I'm going? Eh? Eh?"~ [MO27290V]
@27291 = ~"Chief, we already got an opening line with these limping ladies. We've *all* died at least once: we'll have something to talk about. They'll appreciate men with our kind of death experience."~ [MO27291V]
@27292 = ~"Well... all right, *you* might not be dead, but *I* am. And from where I'm standing, I wouldn't mind sharing a coffin with some of these fine, sinewy cadavers I see here." Morte starts clacking his teeth, as if in anticipation. "'Course, the caretakers would have to part with them first, and that's not likely..."~ [MO27292V]
@27293 = ~"Look, chief. You're still a little addled after your kiss with death. So two bits of advice for you: one, if you got questions, *ask* me, all right?"  ^NNOTE: <SPEAKTO>^-~ [MO27293V]
@27294 = ~"Second, if you're *half* as forgetful as you seem to be, start writing stuff down - whenever you come across something that might be important, jot it down so you don't forget."~ [MO27294V]
@27295 = ~"Yeah, like a journal. If you ever start to get cloudy on important things, like where you are, flip to it and refresh your memory. Got it?"  ^NNOTE: To access your journal, select the journal button on the quick menu. Your journal will automatically be updated throughout the game.^-~ [MO27295V]
@27296 = ~"There should be a scalpel on one of the shelves around here. I'd find it before locking horns with any of the corpses around here."~ [MO27296V]
@27297 = ~"All right, you found the scalpel! Now, go get those corpses... and don't worry, I'll stay back and provide valuable tactical advice."~ [MO27297V]
@27298 = ~"I WILL be helping you. Good advice is hard to come by."~ [MO27298V]
@27299 = ~"Me? I'm a romantic, not a soldier. I'd just get in the way."~ [MO27299V]
@27300 = ~"Eh... all right. I'll help you."  ^NNOTE: If you wish Morte to help you attack, simply make sure the both of you are selected when you attack the corpse. Morte will join in the attack.^-~ [MO27300V]
@27301 = ~"All right, you took care of the right corpse, it looks like. Now you gotta find the key. It should have been on its body. Once we have it, we can get out of here."~ [MO27301V]
@27302 = ~"All right, that's the key. It must fit the lock of one of the doors in the room."~ [MO27302V]
@27911 = ~Morte hisses into your ear: "Lawyer."~ [MO27911V]
@27912 = ~"Sort of a talking encyclopedia, chief. I don't like to talk about it, really."~ [MO27912V]
@27913 = ~Morte waggles his eyebrows and begins to float towards the woman. "That's not all I-"~ [MO27913V]
@27915 = ~"Yeah, yeah. Fine." Morte rolls his eyes and starts to mumble. "Sheesh, I might as well be *dead*..."~ [MO27915V]
@27919 = ~Morte interrupts her: "Well, you see, chief, it's all about differences in the *quality* of your mimir. Some - like me - are more enchanted than others, that's all. More... uh... 'self-aware,' is the term."~ [MO27919V]
@27922 = ~"Hey! I'm just trying to have some fun here, chief!"~ [MO27922V]
@28036 = ~Morte nods appreciatively. "Hey, this guy's not bad."~ [MO28036V]
@28037 = ~Morte nods appreciatively. "Hey, this guy's not bad."~ [MO28037V]
@28630 = ~"Sounds dull."~ [MO28630V]
@28631 = ~"She's a tanar'ri... a succubus, chief."~ [MO28631V]
@28632 = ~"Bar that, fiendling!" Morte clicks his teeth together. "I'm ALL for the succubus coming with us... the powers know *you're* about as fun as passing a caltrop through your bowels."~ [MO28632V]
@28633 = ~"Hey, wait just a minute! *I'm* the one well-versed in the planes! That's my job, chief!"~ [MO28633V]
@28635 = ~"Pleasant on the eyes, maybe! Looks to ME like all some chit has to do is show a little skin, and you'll sign her right up!" Morte falls silent. "Not that I mind that really, I just thought I'd mention it."~ [MO28635V]
@28637 = ~"What my scarred companion meant to say is, the TWO of us... I'm Morte, by the way: my apologies for my companion's rudeness in not introducing us... think it would be an EXCELLENT idea if you came on board. We have plenty of room for a succubus. PLENTY of room."~ [MO28637V]
@28738 = ~"Thanks, chief. I can't tell you how glad I am to be back with you." His voice drips with sarcasm. "And here I learned a new trick while I was there and everything."~ [MO28738V]
@28739 = ~"Really? That's kind of you, boss. Good thinking. You're provisionally forgiven. Just don't do it again."~ [MO28739V]
@28740 = ~"Somehow, I don't believe you for a second. Let's just forget this ever happened. Let's go."~ [MO28740V]
@28741 = ~"Thanks, boss. Let's get out of here!" Morte pauses. "Oh, by the way, boss... those guys really had their heads together. They taught me something sharp."~ [MO28741V]
@28962 = ~"Uh... chief? You've seen statues before, right? Know that they don't talk or anything?"~ [MO28962V]
@28963 = ~"Well... uh... hmm. Got me there, boss."~ [MO28963V]
@28964 = ~"Maybe it's a little too anatomically correct, chief?"~ [MO28964V]
@28965 = ~"Sure, boss. I knew that."~ [MO28965V]
@28966 = ~Morte rolls his eyes and makes a gagging noise. "Powers, no, not another berk that talks... like... this!"~ [MO28966V]
@29677 = ~"Hey, chief - he's got his fingers crossed!"~ [MO29677V]
@30527 = ~Morte breaks in with a whisper. "He's saying he's a lawyer. A counselor. One of those berks who rattle their bone-boxes at the courts."~ [MO30527V]
@30816 = ~Morte turns and looks behind him. "Where?! Where?!"~ [MO30816V]
@30817 = ~Morte gasps. "Look, behind you - another floating skull!"~ [MO30817V]
@30818 = ~"Right where I'm pointing! There!"~ [MO30818V]
@30819 = ~Morte speaks with mock exasperation: "You just missed it! A whole *parade* of them! Probably never happen again in a million revolutions of the Great Ring!"~ [MO30819V]
@30820 = ~Morte bobs slightly, as if shrugging. "I prefer to refer to it as keen insights into human nature."~ [MO30820V]
@30821 = ~"You know, chief, that JUST MIGHT BE CRAZY ENOUGH TO WORK!"~ [MO30821V]
@32367 = ~"'Darks?!' Gimme a break! We're really not going to *listen* to this rattletrap, are we? C'mon... let's go find some Sensate chits that have never had the pleasurous sensation of tasting the fiery passion of a skull's lips." He waggles eyebrows in anticipation.~ [MO32367V]
@32371 = ~Morte whispers: "Beginning of more suffering."~ [MO32371V]
@32376 = ~Morte whispers: "That's for sure."~ [MO32376V]
@32381 = ~Morte whispers: "And eternal boredom."~ [MO32381V]
@32386 = ~Morte whispers: "Looks like we know where we both are going to end up when we die."~ [MO32386V]
@32391 = ~Morte whispers: "And that's if you're lucky."~ [MO32391V]
@32396 = ~Morte whispers: "And that's supposed to be an incentive? We get to do this all *again?* Gee, I can't wait to be a floating skull all over again. Whee! Pike him. What a tard. Spoken just like someone who hasn't died before, huh?"~ [MO32396V]
@32401 = ~Morte whispers: "Oh, this is one, big steaming load."~ [MO32401V]
@32406 = ~Morte says aloud: "What wash!"~ [MO32406V]
@32407 = ~Morte ducks below the lecturer's field of view, then turns to you and whispers: "Go ahead, chief. Tell him the dark of it."~ [MO32407V]
@32410 = ~"Great! Another death! Sign me up!" There is laughter from the audience. The speaker looks angry.~ [MO32410V]
@32651 = ~"Want me to slap this barmy chit down, chief?"~ [MO32651V]
@32652 = ~"I love your addled ways, chief."~ [MO32652V]
@32653 = ~As you kneel before the woman, Morte cries out: "Chief! You're kidding me! I mean, unless, you're *into* that or something..."~ [MO32653V]
@32654 = ~"Well, you've a point there... but still..."~ [MO32654V]
@32655 = ~Morte chuckles and clicks his teeth together. "Just a regular lady's man, eh, chief?"~ [MO32655V]
@32656 = ~"Uh-oh..."~ [MO32656V]
@32657 = ~Morte winks at you and calls to the woman: "Hey, you! That's right, you there, you saucy little tart... look at me when I talk to you! What's got you so bitter, hmm?"~ [MO32657V]
@32658 = ~"Aw, does the little Desert Princess have her britches in a bunch because the Sultan wanted another son? Tell me, 'Desert Princess,' do you spend most of your nights drunken and belligerent, followed about by a handful of leering sycophants, looking in your own pathetic way to justify your existence to a disapproving father?"~ [MO32658V]
@32659 = ~"Do you really think your petty brawling will finally make you feel better about yourself? Feel like you're *worth* something? Because IT WON'T! If this is your sad little path to feeling better about who you *are,* I suggest you just give up, go home, and marry off into some courtier's harem!"~ [MO32659V]
@32660 = ~Morte turns to you. "See, chief, I *know* what's going to happen here. We *all* know Morte's right on the ball with this one. But oh, no, proud little Desert Princess, cut down in public, humiliat-"~ [MO32660V]
@33073 = ~"The Blood War? More boring than listening to a Guvner recite laws. Let's find some young Sensates who need to be indoctrinated in the ways of passion!" He waggles eyebrows in anticipation.~ [MO33073V]
@33300 = ~Morte rolls his eyes and cries "Oye! Look! A talkin' turd!"~ [MO33300V]
@33301 = ~Morte bobs in your direction, speaking to the man: "I was referring to this big scarred-up berk here, blood... not you! No harm done, eh?"~ [MO33301V]
@33423 = ~Morte rolls his eyes and cries "Oye! Look! A talkin' turd!"~ [MO33423V]
@33429 = ~Morte bobs in your direction, speaking to the man: "I was referring to this big scarred-up berk here, blood... not you! No harm done, eh?"~ [MO33429V]
@33961 = ~"Hmmmph. Well, I don't know how long I'm going to wait here, so I'm going to give you one LAST chance. You sure you don't want my sage advice and quick wit?"~ [MO33961V]
@33965 = ~"Are you trying to hurt my feelings, chief? What, was it something I said? The fact I don't have arms? What?"~ [MO33965V]
@33968 = ~"Well, I'm not going to wait FOREVER, so you better come back as soon as you change your mind."~ [MO33968V]
@33970 = ~"What's eating you, chief?"~ [MO33970V]
@34990 = ~"Psssst. You see the way she was looking at me? Huh? You see that? The way she was following the curve of my occipital bone?"~ [MO34990V]
@34992 = ~"Wha- are you BLIND?! She was scouting me out! It was shameless the way she WANTED me."~ [MO34992V]
@34994 = ~"You? Yeah, right! Trust me, chits beyond the grave don't care about all that 'physicality' and 'I've got a body' and 'I'm all scarred and tough-looking.' They want guys with SPIRIT. That's me, chief. You? Corpses like YOU are as common as copper."~ [MO34994V]
@34997 = ~"Yeah, yeah, whatever. When you've been dead as long as I have, you know the signals. They may be too SUBTLE for you to pick up on, but that's why I'll be spending MY nights with some luscious recently-dead chit while you're standing around goin' 'huh?' 'Whatzz goin' on?' 'Where's my muh-muh-memories?'"~ [MO34997V]
