@35310 = ~"Hmmmm. Wonder if this graybeard would mind if *I* borrowed his body..."~ [MO35310V]
@35312 = ~"Graybeard... you know, geezer, old feller, yellow dog... old."~ [MO35312V]
@35314 = ~Morte studies the skeleton for a moment, then shakes his head. "Nah... I'd need a fresher one than this. And something with a little more dignity... this one's all creaky and fractured."~ [MO35314V]
@35316 = ~"Oh, you're a sackfull of laughs." Morte glares at you. "Besides, YOU'RE one to talk, berk. Mirrors beg for mercy when you're around."~ [MO35316V]
@35318 = ~Morte snorts. You're not quite sure how he managed it without lungs.~ [MO35318V]
@35320 = ~"I'll have you know that helping you escape the preparation room has now been added to my growing list of regrets." Morte snorts again. "I should have let you rot... some more, that is."~ [MO35320V]
@35341 = ~"Whoa, chief. That's vandalism. Those bolts are probably the only thing holding that bag of bones together. Necromancy only goes so far with these old fellas, y'know?"~ [MO35341V]
@35343 = ~"Oh, it's not a problem." Morte does a strange bobbing motion that you think might be a shrug. "Just wasn't sure if you knew that or not. By all means, go ahead."~ [MO35343V]
@35387 = ~"Hmmmm. Wonder if this graybeard would mind if *I* borrowed his body..."~ [MO35387V]
