@38265 = ~"I love this chit already!"~ [MO38265V]
@38266 = ~"Yikes!"~ [MO38266V]
@39000 = ~Morte whispers, "This ain't good, chief. Watch your step, or they'll wipe your mind clean out of existence... they're more powerful in bigger groups - each of them adds to a group brain. They're *deadly.*"~ [MO39000V]
@39001 = ~Morte whispers, "This ain't good, chief. Watch your step, or they'll wipe your mind clean out of existence... they're more powerful in bigger groups - each of them adds to a group brain. They're *deadly.*"~ [MO39001V]
@39002 = ~Morte whispers, "I don't know what they're up to, chief, but watch your thoughts. They're a group mind, and each rat adds more to the mind, and they fight like - pardon the expression - cornered rats. We're in their home now, boss, and they've got nowhere to go. Don't mess this up."~ [MO39002V]
@39564 = ~"What a coincidence! I, too, chase tails."~ [MO39564V]
@39565 = ~"Me? Why do *I* have to tell a story?"~ [MO39565V]
@39566 = ~"No, no, I'll do it... I just thought I'd complain a little out of convention. 'Sides, I love the attention."~ [MO39566V]
@39567 = ~"Please! Come on? Pleeeease? It's a great story! Lots of characters, action, foreshadowing and a startling *denouement!*"~ [MO39567V]
@39568 = ~"It is! It is! Come *on!*"~ [MO39568V]
@39569 = ~"Beats me! But it sure *sounds* impressive!"~ [MO39569V]
@39570 = ~"Fine, fine..."~ [MO39570V]
@39571 = ~"An elderly man was sitting alone on a dark path, right? He wasn't certain of which direction to go, and he'd forgotten both where he was traveling to and who he was. He'd sat down for a moment to rest his weary legs, and suddenly looked up to see an elderly woman before him. She grinned toothlessly and with a cackle, spoke: 'Now your *third* wish. What will it be?'"~ [MO39571V]
@39572 = ~"'Third wish?' The man was baffled. 'How can it be a third wish if I haven't had a first and second wish?'"~ [MO39572V]
@39573 = ~"'You've had two wishes already,' the hag said, 'but your second wish was for me to return everything to the way it was before you had made your first wish. That's why you remember nothing; because everything is the way it was before you made any wishes.' She cackled at the poor berk. 'So it is that you have one wish left.'"~ [MO39573V]
@39574 = ~"'All right,' said the man, 'I don't believe this, but there's no harm in wishing. I wish to know who I am.'"  "'Funny,' said the old woman as she granted his wish and disappeared forever. 'That was your first wish.'"~ [MO39574V]
@39575 = ~"What in the hells was that, you stupid polygon?! That's the most boring story I ever heard!"~ [MO39575V]
@39576 = ~"Embellishments?"~ [MO39576V]
@39577 = ~"*C'mon* already, fiendling. You already have one tail you won't part with."~ [MO39577V]
@39795 = ~"Uh... who am *I?* How about *you* start? Who're you?"~ [MO39795V]
@39798 = ~"You can't remember your *name?* Heh. Well, NEXT time you spend a night in this berg, go easy on the bub. Name's Morte. I'm trapped in here, too."~ [MO39798V]
@39800 = ~"Yeah, 'an I asked you *second.* What's your name?"~ [MO39800V]
@39803 = ~"Tchhhh... you're tighter than a wet rope. All right, *I'll* be the nice guy here. Name's Morte. Who're you?"~ [MO39803V]
@39805 = ~"Yeah, since you haven't had time to get your legs yet, here's the chant: I've tried all the doors, and this room is locked tighter than a chastity belt."~ [MO39805V]
@39807 = ~"It's called the 'Mortuary'... it's a big black structure with all the architectural charm of a pregnant spider."~ [MO39807V]
@39809 = ~"Not from where I'm standing. You got scars a-plenty, though... looks like some berk painted you with a knife. All the more reason to give this place the laugh before whoever carved you up comes back to finish the job."~ [MO39809V]
@39811 = ~"Well... the carvings on your chest aren't TOO bad... but the ones on your back..." Morte pauses. "Say, looks like you got a whole tattoo gallery on your back, chief. Spells out something..."~ [MO39811V]
@39813 = ~"Heh! Looks like you come with directions..." Morte clears his throat. "Let's see... it starts with..."  "'I know you feel like you've been drinking a few kegs of Styx wash, but you need to CENTER yourself. Among your possessions is a JOURNAL that'll shed some light on the dark of the matter. PHAROD can fill you in on the rest of the chant, if he's not in the dead-book already.'"~ [MO39813V]
@39815 = ~"Yeah, there's a bit more..." Morte pauses. "Let's see... it goes on..."  'Don't lose the journal or we'll be up the Styx again. And whatever you do, DO NOT tell anyone WHO you are or WHAT happens to you, or they'll put you on a quick pilgrimage to the crematorium. Do what I tell you: READ the journal, then FIND Pharod.'~ [MO39815V]
@39817 = ~"No... you were stripped to the skins when you arrived here. 'Sides, looks like you got enough of a journal penned on your body."~ [MO39817V]
@39819 = ~"Nobody I know... but then again, I don't know many people. Still, SOME berk's got to know where to find Pharod... uh, once we get out of here, that is."~ [MO39819V]
@39821 = ~"Well, all the doors are locked, so we'll need the key. Chances are, one of the walking corpses in this room has it."~ [MO39821V]
@39823 = ~"Yeah, the Mortuary keepers use dead bodies as cheap labor. The corpses are dumb as stones, but they're harmless, and won't attack you unless you attack first."~ [MO39823V]
@39826 = ~"What, you think it's going to hurt their feelings? They're DEAD. But if you want a bright side to this: if you kill them, at least they'll have a rest before their keepers raise them up to work again."~ [MO39826V]
@39828 = ~"Well, before you do that, arm yourself first. I think there's a scalpel on one of the shelves around here."  ^NNOTE: Search the shelves in the room for a weapon to attack the zombies with. <SEARCH_WEAPON>^-~ [MO39828V]
@39830 = ~"One last thing: Those corpses are as slow as molasses, but getting punched by one of them is like being kissed by a battering ram. If they start getting an edge on you, remember you can RUN, and they can't. Use it to keep some distance if you need to recover."  ^NNOTE: <RUNAWAY> If you are in danger of dying, use running to keep your distance from the zombies while you recover.^-~ [MO39830V]
@39832 = ~"There should be a scalpel on one of the shelves around here. I'd find it before locking horns with any of the corpses around here."  ^NNOTE: Search the shelves in the room for a weapon to attack the zombies with. <SEARCH_WEAPON>^-~ [MO39832V]
@39834 = ~"All right, you found the scalpel! Now, go get those corpses... and don't worry, I'll stay back and provide valuable tactical advice."~ [MO39834V]
@39837 = ~"I WILL be helping you. Good advice is hard to come by."~ [MO39837V]
@39840 = ~"Me? I'm a romantic, not a soldier. I'd just get in the way."~ [MO39840V]
@39843 = ~"Eh... all right. I'll help you."  ^NNOTE: If you wish Morte to help you attack, simply make sure the both of you are selected when you attack the corpse. Morte will join in the attack.^-~ [MO39843V]
@39845 = ~"Time to introduce these corpses to the second death, then..."  ^NNOTE: <ATTACKNOTE>^-~ [MO39845V]
@39847 = ~"All right, you took care of the right corpse, looks like. Now you gotta find the key. It should have been on its body. Once we have it, we can get out of here."  ^NNOTE: <DEADPILE>^-~ [MO39847V]
@39849 = ~"All right, that's the key. It must fit the lock of one of the doors in the room."~ [MO39849V]
@39854 = ~"Hmmmph. Well, I don't know how long I'm going to wait here, so I'm going to give you one LAST chance. You sure you don't want my sage advice and quick wit?"~ [MO39854V]
@39858 = ~"Are you trying to hurt my feelings, chief? What, was it something I said? The fact I don't have arms? What?"~ [MO39858V]
@39861 = ~"Well, I'm not going to wait FOREVER, so you better come back as soon as you change your mind."~ [MO39861V]
@40068 = ~Morte spins around you, mocking the girl's obviousness. "Powers above, chief... she's right! I never noticed before... you're covered in *scars!*"~ [MO40068V]
@40074 = ~Morte waggles his eyebrows. "You're too 'forward,' all right... may have something to do with those swaying, pendulous br-"~ [MO40074V]
@40076 = ~Morte shuts up.~ [MO40076V]
@40081 = ~"Hey!"~ [MO40081V]
@40082 = ~Morte mutters to himself. "I guess it's good that there's *something* in there."~ [MO40082V]
@40222 = ~"Oooh, no... you've *got* to tell us, now."~ [MO40222V]
@40275 = ~Morte floats close to you, whispering: "I feel sorry for her lover. He doesn't know how bad he has it. A chit like this is nothing but trouble."~ [MO40275V]
@40685 = ~Morte whispers quietly: "Whoah... creepy chit."~ [MO40685V]
@40846 = ~"C'mon, chief! We're in a building full of some of the sexiest chits this side of the multiverse and you're stopping to talk to *modrons?*"~ [MO40846V]
@40851 = ~Morte makes a noise of utter disgust. "What's there to say? Annoying little clock-work pests... they're always working to impose law and order upon the multiverse. Not *good,* mind you... just *law.* Let's just forget about 'em and go chat up the ladies, eh?"~ [MO40851V]
@40855 = ~Morte sighs loudly. "Fine, whatever - but don't say I didn't warn you. You probably won't get anywhere with 'em though, chief... they're an odd lot to talk to."~ [MO40855V]
@41135 = ~"Anything!" Morte cries. "Do anything you want to me!"~ [MO41135V]
@41136 = ~"It's enough to make me weep... where was this chit when I had a *body?!*"~ [MO41136V]
@41144 = ~"Pssst... Some advice, chief: I'd keep it quiet from here on - no need to put any more corpses in the dead-book than necessary... especially the femmes. Plus, killing them might draw the caretakers here."~ [MO41144V]
@41149 = ~"They call themselves the 'Dustmen.' You can't miss 'em: They have an obsession with black and rigor mortis of the face. They're an addled bunch of ghoulish death-worshippers; they believe everybody should die... sooner better than later."~ [MO41149V]
@41151 = ~"Weren't you listening?! I said the Dusties believe EVERYBODY'S got to die, sooner better than later. You think the corpses you've seen are happier in the dead-book than out of it?"~ [MO41151V]
@41155 = ~"Death visits the planes every day, chief. These shamblers are all that's left of the poor sods who sold their bodies to the caretakers after death."~ [MO41155V]
@41159 = ~"Wh- are you *serious?* Look, chief, these dead chits are the last chance for a couple of hardy bashers like us. We need to be *chivalrous*... no hacking them up for keys, no lopping their limbs off, things like that."~ [MO41159V]
@41161 = ~"Chief, THEY'RE dead, WE'RE dead... see where I'm going? Eh? Eh?"~ [MO41161V]
@41164 = ~"Chief, we already got an opening line with these limping ladies. We've *all* died at least once: we'll have something to talk about. They'll appreciate men with our kind of death experience."~ [MO41164V]
@41166 = ~"Well... all right, *you* might not be dead, but *I* am. And from where I'm standing, I wouldn't mind sharing a coffin with some of these fine, sinewy cadavers I see here." Morte starts clacking his teeth, as if in anticipation. "'Course, the caretakers would have to part with them first, and that's not likely..."~ [MO41166V]
@41170 = ~"Look, chief. It's obvious you're still a little addled after your kiss with death, so I got two bits of advice for you: one, if you got questions, *ask* me, all right?"  ^NNOTE: <SPEAKTO>^-~ [MO41170V]
@41172 = ~"Second, if you're *half* as forgetful as you seem to be, start writing stuff down - whenever you come across something that *might* be important, jot it down so you don't forget."~ [MO41172V]
@41174 = ~"Start a new one, then, chief. No loss. There's plenty of parchment and ink around here to last you."~ [MO41174V]
@41176 = ~"Use it to keep track of your movements. If you ever start to get cloudy on important things, like who you are... or more importantly, who *I* am... use it to refresh your memory."  ^NNOTE: To access your journal, select the journal button on the quick menu. Your journal will automatically be updated throughout the game.^-~ [MO41176V]
@41178 = ~"What's eating you, chief?"~ [MO41178V]
@41188 = ~"Aw, *c'mon,* chief. Don't tell me you forgot already."~ [MO41188V]
@41193 = ~"Bet I'm going to be hearing THAT a lot." Morte clears his throat. "Let's see..."  'I know you feel like you've been drinking a few kegs of Styx wash, but you need to CENTER yourself. Among your possessions is a JOURNAL that'll shed some light on the dark of the matter. PHAROD can fill you in on the rest of the chant, if he's not in the dead-book already.'~ [MO41193V]
@41198 = ~"I will, I will, hold on." Morte pauses for a moment. "All right, here's the last bit..."  'Don't lose the journal or we'll be up the Styx again. And whatever you do, DO NOT tell anyone WHO you are or WHAT happens to you, or they'll put you on a quick pilgrimage to the crematorium. Do what I tell you: READ the journal, then FIND Pharod.'~ [MO41198V]
@41202 = ~"No... you were stripped to the skins. Like I said before, looks like you got enough of a journal penned on your body."~ [MO41202V]
@41208 = ~"Nope. Still, some berk's got to know where to find him. Let's ask around... AFTER we get out of here."~ [MO41208V]
@41212 = ~"It's called the 'Mortuary'... it's a big black structure with all the architectural charm of a pregnant spider."~ [MO41212V]
@41216 = ~"They call themselves the 'Dustmen.' You can't miss 'em: They have an obsession with black and rigor mortis of the face. They're an addled bunch of ghoulish death-worshippers; they believe everybody should die... sooner better than later."~ [MO41216V]
@41221 = ~"Weren't you listening?! I said the Dusties believe EVERYBODY'S got to die, sooner better than later. You think the corpses you've seen are happier in the dead-book than out of it?"~ [MO41221V]
@41225 = ~"You, well... you *use* them. Staunch bleeding, and all that."  ^NNOTE: <BANDAGES2>^-~ [MO41225V]
@41229 = ~"Death visits the planes every day, chief. These shamblers are all that's left of the poor sods who sold their bodies to the caretakers after death."~ [MO41229V]
@41233 = ~"Wh- are you *serious?* Look, chief, these dead chits are the last chance for a couple of hardy bashers like us. We need to be *chivalrous*... no hacking them up for keys, no lopping their limbs off, things like that."~ [MO41233V]
@41237 = ~"Chief, THEY'RE dead, WE'RE dead... see where I'm going? Eh? Eh?"~ [MO41237V]
@41242 = ~"Chief, we already got an opening line with these limping ladies. We've *all* died at least once: we'll have something to talk about. They'll appreciate men with our kind of death experience."~ [MO41242V]
@41246 = ~"Well... all right, *you* might not be dead, but *I* am. And from where I'm standing, I wouldn't mind sharing a coffin with some of these fine, sinewy cadavers I see here." Morte starts clacking his teeth, as if in anticipation. "'Course, the caretakers would have to part with them first, and that's not likely..."~ [MO41246V]
@41250 = ~"I knew you'd be back, chief! Finally realized you needed me, huh?"~ [MO41250V]
@41253 = ~"Hmmmph. Well, I don't know how long I'm going to wait here, so I'm going to give you one LAST chance. You sure you don't want my sage advice and quick wit?"~ [MO41253V]
@41257 = ~"Are you trying to hurt my feelings, chief? What, was it something I said? The fact I don't have arms? What?"~ [MO41257V]
@41260 = ~"Well, I'm not going to wait FOREVER, so you better come back as soon as you change your mind."~ [MO41260V]
@41262 = ~"Powers above. That's one HELL of a book."~ [MO41262V]
@41264 = ~"If I were to guess, I'd say that's the book where they scratch the name of every poor sod that's unfortunate enough to get dumped off here."~ [MO41264V]
@41266 = ~"Eh... well... I *guess.* To find out, you'd need to rattle your bone-box with that floating Dustie over there. I'm not sure that's a good idea."~ [MO41266V]
@41632 = ~"My friend thought you were attractive, but *whoah!* Was he ever horribly mistaken!"~ [MO41632V]
@41633 = ~"Sure, chief, whatever. What a witch, huh?" Morte *hmphs,* then waggles his eyebrows. "I *like* that!"~ [MO41633V]
@41636 = ~"Like I'd let mine anywhere near if I had one! What, did you hear the word 'brothel' and think you could make some jink here, you flea-bitten gutter-whore? Hah! Can't believe they even let you in the door, what with all those ticks hopping off your shaggy legs!"~ [MO41636V]
@41639 = ~"*He!* That's '*HE* seems pretty foul-mouthed,' Kimasxi 'Bladderdung'... you scruffy, goat-gammed harlot!"~ [MO41639V]
@41640 = ~"Better than you, perhaps?" Morte waggles his eyebrows at her. "Eh? Eh?"~ [MO41640V]
@41830 = ~"Look, chief. It's obvious you're still a little addled after your kiss with death, so I got two bits of advice for you: one, if you got questions, *ask* me, all right?"  ^NNOTE: <SPEAKTO>^-~ [MO41830V]
@41832 = ~"Second, if you're *half* as forgetful as you seem to be, start writing stuff down - whenever you come across something that *might* be important, jot it down so you don't forget."~ [MO41832V]
@41834 = ~"Start a new one, then, chief. No loss. There's plenty of parchment and ink around here to last you."~ [MO41834V]
@41836 = ~"Use it to keep track of your movements. If you ever start to get cloudy on important things, like who you are... or more importantly, who *I* am... use it to refresh your memory."  ^NNOTE: To access your journal, select the journal button on the quick menu. Your journal will automatically be updated throughout the game.^-~ [MO41836V]
